  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large cast-iron pan over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the diced onion and cook for 5 minutes, or until lightly charred.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the diced red bell pepper and cook for an additional 2-3 minutes.",
    "Add the chickpeas, smoked paprika, caraway seeds, salt, and tomato paste.",
    "Stir to combine and cook for 2-3 minutes, or until the chickpeas are lightly charred.",
    "Add the chickpea liquid and stir to combine.",
    "Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Taste and adjust seasoning as needed.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped fresh parsley if desired.",
    "Serve with crusty bread or as a side dish."
